    Title: Uncollected Poems
  Locus:
    Daily: December 29
Format: Verse
Description: Lines composed on October 27, 1925 with instructions to be
  carved on the author's gravestone.
Title: The Poet's Epitaph
---
Rose, oh pure paradox, desire
to be no one's sleep beneath
the many eyelids of your petals.
